Sentencas: The in situ exsolution of nanoparticles from perovskite oxides has garnered significant research attention and has been proven to be an effective approach for obtaining high-performance electrode materials for solid oxide cells.
Titulo: Performance of Co-doped Sr1.9FeNbO 6-δ as a symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: In this study, we synthesized a series of double perovskites Sr1.9FeNb1-xCoxO6-delta (x = 0, 0.3, 0.4, 0.5; named as SFN, SFNC03, SFNC04, SFNC05, respectively) by solid state method as electrode materials for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells and symmetrical solid oxide electrolysis cells.
Titulo: Performance of Co-doped Sr1.9FeNbO 6-δ as a symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the impedance of SFNC05 in air and hydrogen atmospheres reached 0.025 and 0.21 Omega cm2, respectively.
Titulo: Performance of Co-doped Sr1.9FeNbO 6-δ as a symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The output performance of the fuel cell with SFNC05 symmetrical electrode reached 806, 687, and 300 mW cm-2 using hydrogen, methanol and propane as fuels, respectively, at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance of Co-doped Sr1.9FeNbO 6-δ as a symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The fuel cell also showed good output performance stability over 100 h in methanol at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance of Co-doped Sr1.9FeNbO 6-δ as a symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: In electrolysis cell mode, the current densities are -1.54 and -1.55 A cm-2 at 2 V for electrolysis CO2 and at 1.3 V for electrolysis seawater, respectively.
Titulo: Performance of Co-doped Sr1.9FeNbO 6-δ as a symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The output performance does not degrade significantly for electrolysis CO2 and seawater during 200 h stability test.
Titulo: Performance of Co-doped Sr1.9FeNbO 6-δ as a symmetrical electrode for solid oxide cells
